  vulnerability involving a trivially forgeable admin authentication cookie was
  fixed by implementing an HMAC-based session system using the Web Crypto API to
  ensure compatibility with Vercel's Edge Runtime. Other bugs included fixing
  NaN values and minute calculations in PDF generation, allowing null values for
  empty number inputs, enabling a 'Download PDF' button, and replacing a
  hardcoded user name in PDFs. API routes were secured with pagination
  validation, and CSV exports were capped to prevent memory issues. The
  persistent Vercel deployment failures were eventually traced to a missing
   configuration in the Prisma schema, which was then added. The
  agent ensured all fixes were committed, pushed, and verified through local
  builds and CI/CD checks, resulting in a fully functional and secure
  application.
